Visit scenic Mongo before Ming's rise to power! In this prequel to the critically acclaimed and best-selling FLASH GORDON: ZEITGEIST, Prince Ming begins his rise to dominion over the entirety of Mongo! Collected in Merciless: The Rise of Ming.

deck: French translation of the Japanese Abara manga.
description:
Made famous by Blame!, his cult series, Tsutomu Nihei has become a must-SF writer, graphics and layout unique. His stories are bathed in a stifling atmosphere that makes it even more oppressive breathtaking scenery, creatures half-human, half-synthetic and monstrous characters to a panel of inhumanity disturbing. Abara is the name of one of his works among the latest. The Shiro Gauna mutant creatures are shapeshifters who spread terror in a futuristic city. Based on their spines, armor made ​​of indestructible bones envelops the body of their owner and spreads in all directions, attacking all forms of life nearby. What is the origin of this monstrosity? A woman and a man that separates all will try to penetrate this secret short work in two volumes, Abara extends nightmarish delusions of Blame! By setting the bar even higher. A real slap visual.

French translation of the original Japanese Abara manga.
name: Abara

Written by:

Paul Levitz (#1 - Present)

Illustrated by:

George Perez (#1 - Present)

Kevin Maguire (#1 - Present)

  • Vol. 3: Control Issues (#13-18)
